          @neumi17 In defense of Schmelzer (2of2) It's because Schmelzer does cover the space efficiently that Tuchel needs him there. He has an exceptional timing and very good decision making skills. His contribution in the build up has gained much quality in the last years and his passing skills have improved. Just take a look at his passes in the spaces between the lines. Both his speed and his tactical intelligence are essential for Dortmund's possession football high up the pitch. He makes the right runs in order to pressure the defense and to create space for the technically gifted attacking midfielders; and his pace allows him to recover quickly in defence. That's my two cents.
